Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Once hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel the @garlic{2%cloves}, pop it into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. Add the potato tray and roast in the oven until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}. Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1} and reserve 1 leaf per person. Halve the remaining lettuce lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on a medium-high heat. When hot, lay in the @streaky bacon rashers{6} and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}. Meanwhile, pop the @British pork and oregano sausage meat{225%g} into a medium #bowl{} and season with @pepper{}. Roll the meat into even-sized balls then shape into 1cm thick burgers (1 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

When hot, add the burgers and fry until browned and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} on each side. Turn them every ~{2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Carefully place half the grated cheese on top of the burgers. Cover with a #lid{} (or wrap loosely in foil), then set aside, off the heat, for ~{3-4%minutes} for the cheese to melt.

When the wedges have ~{5%minutes} left, chop up 1 rasher of crispy bacon per person. Sprinkle the chopped bacon and remaining cheese over the wedges. Bake until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Once the garlic is cooked, remove from the foil and mash with a #fork{}. Pop it into a large bowl with the @water{1/2%cup} and half the @mayonnaise{1}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix well. Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and chopped baby gem and toss to coat.

Halve the @glazed burger buns{2} and pop in the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}. Spread the remaining mayo on the warmed bun bases, then top with a whole lettuce leaf and a burger. Finish with 2 rashers of crispy bacon each, then spread the @onion marmalade{20%g} onto the bun lids and pop them on top. Serve with the wedges and slaw alongside. Enjoy!